uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.reference

Class IndexedReference<I extends Indexed>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.reference.IndexedReference<I>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - 

    public final class IndexedReference<I extends Indexed>
extends java.lang.Object
    A lightweight class that holds the id of an Indexed type and enough information to create the target object. This is intended to be as efficient as using and Integer object but with better type safety and the ability to retrieve the target directly. An id of zero always denotes an unknown value. Note that IndexedSQLValue will generate a IndexedReference with id of zero for a null reference We can't implement a sensible sort order (other than numeric) without an AppContext reference. It is therefore better not to implement Comparable as higher level code (such as table) can but will default to a Comparable implementation if it is implemented. If numeric sorting is required use a ReferenceComparator.
    Author:
    spb
